<Author>zagat
<Content>Great location in Mitte The smallest rooms are really small. Take a step up and it's worth the extra price, especially if you snag a room that faces the quiet and lovely courtyard, way more peaceful than the street-side entrance, which faces a tram stop. All in all, I liked the hotel, though it lacks personality. The location in Mitte can't be beat - very central, yet also tucked away on a side street, so you are away from the bustle when you leave each morning and return each night. I eventually switched hotels and stayed in Prenzlauer Berg, which seemed more vital and less commercial than what Mitte has become over the past few years, but this being Berlin, I fear P'berg is just a year or two behind.... 
