<Author>Klamson
<Content>Great hotel, great location We stayed here for 3 nights, June 15th - 17th. Hackescher Markt Hotel is ideally located. It's within walking distances of many attractions or you can walk about 1/2 block to the train station. Many restaurants, even Starbucks, are located within a block or so. As is the case with many hotels in Europe, rooms are not air conditioned, but stay here in Winter, Fall, early Summer, or spring. We enjoyed out room on the top floor (there is an elevator) with lovely dormer windows that swing open giving a great breeze. It was hot here during the day but wonderfully cool breeze in the evening and all night. Service was excellent, staff very friendly and helpful. Breakfast was wonderful and included in the room rate. There is secure underground parking provided for a fee, located about 1 1/2 blocks away.I'll definitely stay here again when we return to Berlin! 
