<Content>Great Hotel - Great Location What a neighbourhood! Hackeescher Markt Hotel is in a fabulous and trendy part of Berlin. I booked our reservation by phone. The location is great for sight seeing and shopping. Our room was quiet, bright and clean. The bed and pillows were extremely comfortable. There is a cozy bar just beside the lobby with big windows. The staff was helpful and friendly. We joined a New Berlin walking tour at the New Synagogue- just down the street. Our English-speaking tour guide (Kristian) was originally from Toronto. He took us through the old Jewish Neighbourhood and other parts of Mitte. He was extremely friendly, knowledgeable and entertaining. His knowledge of Berlin and European History was impressive. After our four hour tour, he dropped us off at the hotel. 
