<Content>This is The place! TMy wife and I recently (May, 2006) spent eight days in Berlin where we stayed at this gem of a small botique hotel. If you are looking to spend in the $ 175.00-$ 200.00 per night range, you can not beat this place.The staff of Michael, Thorsten, Sabrina and their associates could not do enough for us. They suggested great restaurants and interesting places to see as well as provided us with easy directions. I would recommend getting a room facing the interior garden. It is quieter and nicer than the alternatives.While I am sure one can get less expensive rooms in Berlin, Hackeshcer Markt is well worth every Euro! The location is fantastic--a short walk to all the museums on Museum Isle, 20 minutes or so from the Brandenburg gate and Eastern boundary of the Tiergarten, directly near (2 minutes away) from a major S-bahn stop, five minutes away from where the boats leave for rides on the River Spree , just off a very happenin' square, and ten minutes from the Neue SynagogueThe breakfast alone is worth about $ 25.00 per person and can last (if you want) until dinner.I have rarely been treated better at any place I have stayed in the over 40 years I have travelled in Europe.Arnold MillerPittsburgh,Pa. 
