<Author>Anita1967
<Content>A great little find in Mitte Just returned from a wonderful 3 night stay at the Hachescher Markt hotel. Hotel in a fantastic location - within walking distance of Hachescher Hof courtyards, cafes, bars, restaurants, river. Brandenburg Gate about a 30 minute stroll away down Unter der Linden. We didn't need to use public transport once apart from taxis to and from the airport. Rooms are very clean and a good size. Bathrooms are modern. Remember to ask for a room at the back of the hotel overlooking the courtyard rather than the front. Don't let the trams parked outside the front of the hotel put you off. Bar wasn't open when we stayed but this doesn't matter as there is such a choice on your doorstep. Breakfasts are fab - a great selection and fresh food. Staff are very friendly and speak good English. Had a wonderful meal at the Noodle Bar overlooking the river and the very impressive Berliner Dom - about a 10 minute walk from the hotel. We didn't realise it was part of the Radisson chain but the interior was very modern, staff extremely friendly and they had a wonderful cigar lounge at the back of the bar. Would definitely go back to this hotel - location, location, location as well as friendly service! 
